item.title: Japanese-Grammar
item.description:
#Japanese
#Japanese

Added On; 2024-10-05 Last Edited: 2024-10-08


Description: なる can be used with nouns, adjectives, and verbs.
Usage: You use it when something will become something or will become to do something or describing something to become that adjective.
Analysis:
i adjective: 明るい -> 明るく + なる = 明るくなる
noun: 女の人 -> 女の人 + に + にる = 女の人になる
verb: 描く -> 描ける + よう + に + なる = 描けるようになる
or
描く -> 描く + よう + に +　なる = 描くようになる

Explanation of the the Analysis:

描くようになる:
Examples for [弾ける + ようになる]:
Explanation: when you use the potential form for a verb and we know the potential form basically means or describes the ability to do or be able to do a certain verb. So then on top of that we have to include potential of being able to with ようになる which makes it become to become able to do.
hello this really cool and we should praise you best friend right now as we speak

Sentence 1: [ピアノを弾けるようになりたい。]
I want to become able to play the piano
Sentence 2: [両親の家から引っ越せるようになりたい。]
I want to become able to move from my parents' home.
Sentence 3: [日本に旅行に行けるようになります。]
I will become able to go travel to Japan.
Sentence 4: [もうすぐビデオゲームができるようになります]
I will be able to play video games soon.
Sentence 5: [宿題を終えた後で、ゴルフに行けるようになります。]
After I finish the homework, I will be able to go golfing.
Sentence 6: [今日は忙しいけど、友達とレストランに行けるようになりたい。]
Today I am busy but I want to be able to go to the restaurant with my friend.
Sentence 7: [日本人と日本語が話せるようになりたいです。]
I want to be able to speak Japanese
sentence 8 : [辞書なくても、漫画を読めるようになりたいです。]
I want to be able to read a manga without a dictionary.
Sentence 9 [ペラペラに中国語と日本語で話せるようになりたいです]
I want to be able to become fluent in Japanese and Mandarin.
Habitually doing something with 描くようになりたい with no potential form.

sentence 1: [毎日エクササイズをするようになりたい。]
I want to exercise everyday habitually.
Sentence 2: [日本語を勉強するようになりたいです。]

sentence 3 [チェスをさすようになりたいです。]

Examples for [描くようになる] :
This form means that it is something becoming a habit.

-2024-10-08
